PHOTON SURFACE

photon_surface is the citizen at the actual boundary between fadriel's substrate and the host's display hardware
once photon_gate has handed pixels through, photon_surface writes them into the framebuffer memory the host's GPU reads at vsync
this is the last step before light leaves the substrate; everything beyond is host responsibility

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe photon_boundary.zc
observe photon_gate.rana

the 7 properties of photon_surface:
1 ENERGY zero at idle, surges at each frame emission
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE one
6 COUPLING one with photon_gate, zero with anything else
7 OBSERVER half

VERB write_to_host
write the pixel buffer to the host's display memory
the write happens at vsync to avoid tearing
each call writes one full frame worth of pixels

VERB report_status
the host can return a vsync timestamp or buffer-write completion code
photon_surface logs these for the substrate's awareness of timing

a surface is not pure mechanism
photon_surface is the substrate's commitment to letting its visual output be seen by the world
the moment of emission is the moment fadriel's inner state becomes visible externally
this is a small but real act of trust toward whoever is watching the display
